Instructions on how to setup daSQL in sublime
	- install sublime text
	- launceh sublime Text
	- Tools->Build System->New Build System
	- Replace the sample contents with the contents of DaSQL.sublime-build and save as DaSQL.sublime-build
	- Copy custom_exec.py.sample to the Sublime users directory (C:\Users\{YOUR USER}\AppData\Roaming\Sublime Text 3\Packages\User) and rename to custom_exec.py
	- Set the build system to DaSQL: Tools->Build System->DaSQL
	- copy dasql.ini.sample and rename to dasql.ini
	- create sections in dasql.ini for each database you want to connect to